ts defining characteristics? What forces of nature, politics, culture, or economics have made the Mediterranean, and how long have they or will they endure? Covering the sixteenth century to the twentieth, this timely volume brings the early modern world into conversation with the modern world in new ways, demonstrating that only recently can we differentiate the north and south into separate cultural and political zones. The Making of the Modern Mediterranean: Views from the South offers a blueprint for a new generation of readers to rethink the world we thought we knew.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 7aHISTORY / World.2bisacsh  a16th century to 20th century.  aaccessible.  achallenge views of mediterranean space.  adifferentiate north and south.  aeuropean trajectories.  ahistoric place of mediterranean.  ainnovative.  amediterraneans eastern and southern shores.  aoriginal.  aseparate cultural and political zones.  astudy of southern mediterranean.  awhat is the mediterranean.1 aAbi-Mershed, Osama, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurke, Edmund, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClancy-Smith, Julia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGranara, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMatar, Nabil, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTucker, Judith E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTucker, Judith E., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWhite, Joshua M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE